from shutil import copyfileobj
from urllib import request


import datetime
 
dt_ref = datetime.datetime.combine(datetime.date(year=2020, month=11, day=8), datetime.time(hour=14, minute=0, second=0))
dt_ref_fin = datetime.datetime.combine(datetime.date(year=2020, month=11, day=9), datetime.time(hour=14, minute=0, second=0))

start_date = dt_ref
end_date = dt_ref_fin

while start_date < end_date:
       
    if dt_ref.time()==datetime.time(hour=15, minute=0, second=0):
        print(dt_ref.strftime("%Y%m%d_%H%M%S"))
        liste_horaire.append(dt_ref.strftime("%Y%m%d_%H%M%S"))
        liste_horaire_V0.append(dt_ref.strftime("%Y%m%d%H%M%S"))        
        liste_horaire_V1.append(dt_ref.strftime("%Y-%m-%d_%H:%M:%S"))
        liste_horaire_V2.append(dt_ref)
        url = "https://www.vendeeglobe.org/download-race-data/vendeeglobe_"+dt_ref.strftime("%Y%m%d_%H%M%S")+".xlsx"
        filename = "vendeeglobe_"+dt_ref.strftime("%Y%m%d_%H%M%S")+".xlsx"
        with request.urlopen(url) as response, open(filename, 'wb') as out_file:
            copyfileobj(response, out_file)        
        dt_ref += datetime.timedelta(minutes=120)
        
    if dt_ref.time()==datetime.time(17, 0):
        liste_horaire.append(dt_ref.strftime("%Y%m%d_%H%M%S"))
        liste_horaire_V0.append(dt_ref.strftime("%Y%m%d%H%M%S"))

import uuid

import xlwings as xw

# lecture/écriture d'un fichier Excel avec xlwings
def save_with_xlwings(file):
    tempfile = f'./xlwinf_{file}'
    excel_app = xw.App(visible=False)
    excel_book = excel_app.books.open(file)
    excel_book.save(tempfile)
    excel_book.close()
    excel_app.quit()
    return tempfile
